METHODS: A solid-state Ti:Sapphire femtosecond laser system was integrated in an inverted JenLab Femt-O-Cut laser scanning microscope. A diffraction-limited 40x objective was used to induce multiphoton ionization and plasma production. New Zealand albino rabbits and porcine eyes were used. Surgical outcomes were determined using frame and line scans with nanojoule pulses at a wavelength of 800 nm.
