	abstract = {BACKGROUND AND AIM OF THE STUDY: The Sorin Perceval S (SP) sutureless bioprosthesis was developed as an advancement of conventional biological aortic valve replacement (AVR) with stented bioprostheses, and perhaps also as an alternative to the transcatheter aortic valve implantation (TAVI) procedure, especially for high-risk patients. Herein are described the authors' early results with SP valve replacement, compared to AVR with Carpentier-Edwards Perimount (EP) stented valves.
