RESULTS: 289 infants were included: 150 in the NIV group and 139 in the SURF\&MV group. Seventeen infants in the NIV group and 23 in the SURF\&MV group developed BPD (odds ratio: 1.55; 95\% confidence interval (CI): 0.79-3.05; p = 0.202). After adjusting for potential confounders, the odds ratio was 1.09 for the SURF\&MV group to develop BPD (95\% CI: 0.52-2.28; p = 0.812).
