RESULTS: We used in vivo data from one context (CCl(4) rats with drug treatments) to optimize the computation of E(predict). This optimized relationship was independently validated using in vivo data from two different contexts (treatment of DMN rats and prevention of CCl(4) induction). A linear in vitro-in vivo correlation was consistently observed in all the three contexts. We used E(predict) values to cluster drugs according to efficacy; and found that high-efficacy drugs tended to target proliferation, apoptosis and contractility of HSCs.
